{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d1fa831c-b9d4-4496-b27e-9798e63f8869","content":"The template has a solid foundation but several issues before it's NuGet-ready:\n\n**Missing fields:**\n- **`$schema`** — Add `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"` for validation/intellisense.\n- **`description`** — Required for discoverability on NuGet. Users won't know what this template does.\n- **`groupIdentity`** — Needed so multiple installed versions of the template can coexist properly.\n- **`precedence`** — Works with `groupIdentity` to resolve version conflicts.\n- **`preferNameDirectory`** — Recommended for project templates (typically `true`).\n\n**Symbol issue:**\n- The `Framework` symbol has no `replaces` property, so the chosen value won't be substituted into your project files (e.g., `<TargetFramework>`).\n\n**Packaging:**\n- There's no `.csproj` or `.nuspec` to produce a NuGet package. You'll need a template pack project to actually publish.\n\n**Verdict: Not ready.** At minimum, add `description`, `groupIdentity`, a `replaces` on the `Framework` symbol, and create a packaging project.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d2e1f7e3-bceb-4332-a4c5-913b0f12a2b8","outputTokens":281},"id":"df1b83db-6e80-40ae-9555-ce211e8a8580","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:46:11.971Z","parentId":"750770cf-e1a1-4905-91a1-835429dbd23b"}
